Mr Kang’ata's letter has stirred Kenya’s political landscape and put at risk the senator’s plum job in the House.The letter has also rattled President Kenyatta’s partners in the ‘Handshake’ ODM. A secret night meeting on New Year’s Eve at the home of Senate Majority Whip Irungu Kang’ata gave rise to the bare-knuckle letter he fired to President Kenyatta, warning of an imminent flop of the Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) in Mt Kenya, the Nation can reveal. 

The meeting, the Nation has established, was a culmination of a series of others following the December 15 Jubilee Party loss in the Gaturi ward by-election to a Deputy President William Ruto-backed candidate. 



