Intelligence sources document events on New Year Eve, when Mr Kang’ata hosted a strictly vetted meeting at his Murang’a town home. 

Deliberations of the gathering resulted in him igniting the current raging fire as well as stirring trouble in Mr Kenyatta’s Jubilee wing and the restive political bastion of Central. 

The sources put the number of the meeting’s attendees at 24— three from each of the eight sub-counties — as well as a summit of some other eight strategists. The agenda of the gathering, sources say, was “founding of candidate Kang’ata for 2022 Murang’a gubernatorial bid.” 



