Mr Joshua Kimani from Kigumo sub-county confirmed to Nation that the lawmaker was informed that the ground was so much in favour of the Tangatanga faction that backs Dr Ruto’s presidential bid in 2022. 

Stormy night meeting 

“The senator urged us to be as truthful possible with him because he wanted to ensure his 2022 contest for Murang’a governor would be premised on the political pulse of the county. We were all unanimous that; first, he was in the wrong wing of politics. We told him point-blank that how he was used by Kieleweke to de-whip Tangatanga loyalists had eroded his standing in Murang’a and that, unless he remedied the situation, he was walking into his political gallows,” he said. 

He was reminded that there had been public chaos pitting Tangatanga and Kieleweke supporters, the climax being the October 4 incident in Kenol town where two youths allied to Kieleweke were allegedly murdered by Tangatanga followers. 

“We made our case very well and backed it with actual evidence that is in public domain. We told Kang’ata that if the Kieleweke 2022 ticket was the one being sold by the Handshake team with Mr Raila Odinga as President and Peter Kenneth as his running mate, then he had better kiss his Murang’a gubernatorial ambitions goodbye,” Mr Kimani told Nation, adding that they reminded him that he was yet to lose a political contest. 



