“He started holding meetings on the ground. He would be in night meetings too and we became interested. He started asking around extensively about BBI and its chances, ratings of the President, Mr Peter Kenneth, Mr Odinga and Dr Ruto. He was a man who was walking a defining journey and we are not at all surprised by this turn of events that have culminated in the explosive letter,” said a source. 

Mr Kang’ata Wednesday confirmed to Nation that he hosted the meeting in his Grogan home. Senate Majority Chief Whip says he did not give the letter to any media outlet. Sources said the letter was written after consultation with leaders supporting Mr Kenyatta. All funds will be channelled directly through implementing partners. International broadcaster changes edits and removes some quotes.